1
00:00:44,711 --> 00:00:45,412
And what is this?

2
00:00:45,412 --> 00:00:47,781
Didn't I tell you to ask me before doing anything?

3
00:00:48,014 --> 00:00:49,616
Can I just have my own life?

4
00:00:50,016 --> 00:00:53,153
You are Tao Sor, you love Kim.

5
00:00:53,153 --> 00:00:54,421
He is your boyfriend.

6
00:00:54,421 --> 00:00:55,989
I'll be right beside you.

7
00:00:55,989 --> 00:00:58,458
What can I do to get Kim out of Tao Sor's life?

8
00:00:58,591 --> 00:01:00,827
Do you want him to have memories?

9
00:01:00,827 --> 00:01:03,463
Or are you afraid that his memories will come back?

10
00:01:03,696 --> 00:01:05,131
Let's make a wish together.

11
00:01:05,131 --> 00:01:08,301
And if I asked "Who is Kim?" how would you answer?

12
00:01:08,935 --> 00:01:10,670
You know the person in this drawing?

13
00:01:10,670 --> 00:01:13,940
I just dreamt that this boy saved another boy from drowning.

14
00:01:16,776 --> 00:01:19,012
You don't have to go, I'll take the clients myself.

15
00:01:19,012 --> 00:01:21,081
Hurry back!

16
00:01:22,982 --> 00:01:25,552
Is there a problem? What did KIm do?

17
00:01:26,052 --> 00:01:27,754
I just want to know where my brother is.

18
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:29,456
If anything happens to him,

19
00:01:29,823 --> 00:01:32,092
I won't be doing any more business with Siam Sea.

20
00:01:32,225 --> 00:01:33,793
Sang, go check.

21
00:01:34,427 --> 00:01:35,361
Okay, Dad.

22
00:01:48,441 --> 00:01:49,409
It's true, Dad.

23
00:01:49,876 --> 00:01:50,877
There's one ship out right now.

24
00:01:51,878 --> 00:01:53,713
It's the one with the issues.

25
00:01:54,747 --> 00:01:55,548
What did you say?

26
00:01:56,316 --> 00:01:57,750
A faulty ship?

27
00:01:58,218 --> 00:02:00,120
And you just let my brother go?!

28
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:04,057
I just found out as well, like you!

29
00:02:06,292 --> 00:02:07,494
Let's do this, Dad.

30
00:02:07,694 --> 00:02:09,395
I'll hurry and get some people to go look for them.

31
00:02:09,529 --> 00:02:10,029
Get to it!
I'll go too!

32
00:04:00,137 --> 00:04:02,806
What the hell did you just do? You know what you did?!

33
00:04:03,373 --> 00:04:06,376
Tao Sor's terrified of the ocean, you never knew that?!

34
00:04:07,211 --> 00:04:10,647
If something happens to my brother, how will you take responsibility?

35
00:04:10,781 --> 00:04:11,615
I'm sorry...

36
00:04:11,715 --> 00:04:13,383
I won't accept your apology!

37
00:04:14,184 --> 00:04:16,019
People like you never learn.

38
00:04:16,453 --> 00:04:19,423
Otherwise you wouldn't risk Tao Sor's life over and over like this.

39
00:04:19,423 --> 00:04:22,326
But this was an accident!

40
00:04:22,392 --> 00:04:23,293
And another thing.

41
00:04:24,328 --> 00:04:25,963
Tao Sor wanting to remember things,

42
00:04:27,064 --> 00:04:28,499
that's what he needs.

43
00:04:28,665 --> 00:04:29,933
Don't be making excuses!

44
00:04:30,434 --> 00:04:33,270
Everything that happened is because of you, and only you!

45
00:04:33,337 --> 00:04:33,937
Hey!

46
00:04:35,172 --> 00:04:36,340
Kim already said so,

47
00:04:37,341 --> 00:04:39,376
that your brother went to go see him on his own will.

48
00:04:39,877 --> 00:04:43,413
You can't just blame us for this incident.

49
00:04:44,314 --> 00:04:46,016
So you're gonna protect a guilty person?

50
00:04:46,550 --> 00:04:48,285
You're protecting your brother,

51
00:04:48,619 --> 00:04:50,020
I'm protecting mine!

52
00:04:51,088 --> 00:04:52,456
There's no difference.

53
00:05:01,231 --> 00:05:04,568
We truly apologize for this whole situation.

54
00:05:05,235 --> 00:05:07,471
I might not fully understand how you feel,

55
00:05:08,105 --> 00:05:09,106
but I think...

56
00:05:10,107 --> 00:05:11,308
Kim's feelings...

57
00:05:12,409 --> 00:05:13,710
knowing that he's the reason

58
00:05:14,511 --> 00:05:15,846
someone he loves is hurt...

59
00:05:18,849 --> 00:05:20,651
it would hurt so much.

60
00:05:21,251 --> 00:05:25,088
Okay. From now on, don't ever let these two meet again.

61
00:05:25,188 --> 00:05:27,591
Otherwise we're going to take legal action.

62
00:05:28,725 --> 00:05:33,463
And The Treasure will nullify every business deal with Siam Sea.

63
00:05:33,730 --> 00:05:35,265
Starting from today.

64
00:05:39,903 --> 00:05:40,671
Okay.

65
00:05:44,741 --> 00:05:48,445
My professor says he's in a stable condition, but he's not awake.

66
00:05:49,813 --> 00:05:51,915
Let's go check on Tao Sor.

67
00:05:58,088 --> 00:06:00,824
Hey, you still don't get it?

68
00:06:02,793 --> 00:06:05,228
You have no right to go see him ever again.

69
00:06:07,064 --> 00:06:07,831
Go home.

70
00:06:22,045 --> 00:06:24,181
Please wake up, Son. DOn't let go.

71
00:06:24,948 --> 00:06:28,685
How many times to I have to lose you? I can't lose you again!

72
00:06:33,991 --> 00:06:34,858
Mom?

73
00:06:35,859 --> 00:06:37,194
You shoud go back and rest.

74
00:06:38,095 --> 00:06:39,863
I'll help look after him here.

75
00:06:40,731 --> 00:06:41,431
Okay?

76
00:07:07,824 --> 00:07:08,825
Tao Sor...

77
00:07:12,095 --> 00:07:13,463
you can hear me, right?

78
00:07:16,033 --> 00:07:17,134
Forget everything.

79
00:07:18,902 --> 00:07:21,405
And come back to being my brother, okay?

80
00:07:49,433 --> 00:07:51,968
It's been cleared up, Dad. But...

81
00:07:53,236 --> 00:07:55,472
they won't be doing any more business with us from now on.

82
00:07:56,106 --> 00:07:59,776
This isn't called 'cleared up', we just lost clients!

83
00:08:03,113 --> 00:08:04,314
How are you doing, Kim?

84
00:08:04,448 --> 00:08:07,451
What are you asking him for?! All he's done is cause trouble!

85
00:08:08,185 --> 00:08:10,353
But we're not the only ones at fault here, Dad!

86
00:08:10,654 --> 00:08:13,724
Their son came on his own, boarded the ship on his own,

87
00:08:14,124 --> 00:08:16,426
most importantly, they're above the age of consent!

88
00:08:16,693 --> 00:08:19,496
I don't care! Just go apologize already!

89
00:08:21,298 --> 00:08:22,132
Sang.

90
00:08:24,668 --> 00:08:25,368
I'm sorry.

91
00:08:31,374 --> 00:08:33,276
If you really feel bad,

92
00:08:33,410 --> 00:08:34,778
then I beg you.

93
00:08:35,512 --> 00:08:38,014
Quit messing with that family's son!

94
00:08:42,953 --> 00:08:44,187
Let's go, Dad.

95
00:08:45,021 --> 00:08:46,456
Take your meds and go to sleep.

96
00:08:57,567 --> 00:08:59,169
Calm down, Kim.

97
00:09:11,915 --> 00:09:14,351
I'm on your side, you know?

98
00:09:16,686 --> 00:09:17,654
Thanks...

99
00:09:27,130 --> 00:09:33,069
Happy Birthday to you....

100
00:09:34,004 --> 00:09:35,806
You know the person in this drawing?

101
00:09:40,744 --> 00:09:41,778
Are you okay?

102
00:09:56,259 --> 00:09:59,896
I just dreamt that this boy saved another boy from drowning.

103
00:10:11,474 --> 00:10:12,142
Tao Sor.

104
00:10:16,580 --> 00:10:17,514
It's me.

105
00:10:17,948 --> 00:10:19,015
Your older brother.

106
00:10:19,649 --> 00:10:20,884
I drowned, right?

107
00:10:22,619 --> 00:10:24,020
Someone made you drown.

108
00:10:26,423 --> 00:10:28,325
And someone drowned along with me too, right?

109
00:10:31,494 --> 00:10:32,462
No.

110
00:10:33,463 --> 00:10:34,631
But I saw...

111
00:10:35,899 --> 00:10:37,901
a boy drowning...

112
00:10:39,502 --> 00:10:41,972
and another one came to help...

113
00:10:43,173 --> 00:10:45,475
You must be confused about things.

114
00:10:46,443 --> 00:10:49,212
And...do you remember anything else?

115
00:10:54,951 --> 00:10:55,819
It's okay.

116
00:10:56,219 --> 00:10:57,654
Just forget about all this.

117
00:10:59,389 --> 00:11:01,291
We're gonna go back to being a happy family.

118
00:11:03,093 --> 00:11:05,528
I won't let anything hurt you again.

119
00:11:34,291 --> 00:11:36,326
You're really gonna go through like this?

120
00:11:38,995 --> 00:11:40,530
Yeah, I am.

121
00:11:40,864 --> 00:11:44,668
Anything that is a picture of our parents or me, get rid of it all.

122
00:11:46,503 --> 00:11:49,105
Tao Sor has no need for these memories.

123
00:11:49,506 --> 00:11:50,740
If it isn't of us.

124
00:11:53,009 --> 00:11:57,614
You think by doing this, Tao Sor will truly be happy?

125
00:11:57,981 --> 00:12:00,817
We must clear out anything that can destroy his life.

126
00:12:02,819 --> 00:12:03,653
Let's go.

127
00:12:50,967 --> 00:12:54,537
Chef Mochi, how are you doing?

128
00:12:56,573 --> 00:12:57,874
Who are you?

129
00:12:58,608 --> 00:13:02,045
I'm Chef Daiji, I'm your buddy!

130
00:13:04,781 --> 00:13:06,316
Who's Chef Mochi?

131
00:13:07,250 --> 00:13:08,084
I'm Tao Sor.

132
00:13:10,954 --> 00:13:11,654
Whatever.

133
00:13:12,255 --> 00:13:13,223
Look!

134
00:13:13,957 --> 00:13:16,926
See? I brought you your favorite!

135
00:13:21,898 --> 00:13:23,166
I also brought this!

136
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:24,834
Here...

137
00:13:25,268 --> 00:13:27,170
So you can draw to pass the time.

138
00:13:29,806 --> 00:13:31,007
Thank you.

139
00:13:36,379 --> 00:13:37,747
You're doing fine, right?

140
00:13:42,085 --> 00:13:44,587
Someone left a parcel for you.

141
00:14:46,149 --> 00:14:47,250
It's gonna hurt a bit, okay?

142
00:14:47,323 --> 00:14:48,123
If...

143
00:14:48,891 --> 00:14:52,895
this will be the only thing that will let me remmber today, I'll glady do it.

144
00:14:53,162 --> 00:14:56,765
Blue whales are sybols of solitude.

145
00:14:57,066 --> 00:15:00,269
But when two blue whales meet,

146
00:15:00,736 --> 00:15:05,040
it's like meeting a certain person, where even in a world so large...

147
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:06,642
there'll be someone that truly understands us.

148
00:15:07,009 --> 00:15:08,177
It's so you'll know...

149
00:15:09,244 --> 00:15:11,413
that you'll always have me by your side.

150
00:15:31,767 --> 00:15:32,801
Talay?

151
00:15:33,268 --> 00:15:36,271
This tattoo, how did I get it?

152
00:15:37,006 --> 00:15:38,807
Oh, it's just that the other day...

153
00:15:39,241 --> 00:15:41,910
you said you wanted to get a tattoo, so I took you.

154
00:15:43,645 --> 00:15:44,613
And...

155
00:15:47,149 --> 00:15:48,784
why did I choose the design?

156
00:15:51,353 --> 00:15:54,356
Well, the owner gave you some designs to choose from,

157
00:15:55,157 --> 00:15:58,394
and you thought this one was nice, so you picked this one.

158
00:16:01,663 --> 00:16:02,431
Okay.

159
00:16:10,457 --> 00:16:12,993
We've been here before?

160
00:16:13,427 --> 00:16:15,162
Back then, you were so afraid of the ocean,

161
00:16:15,629 --> 00:16:16,964
so I took you here.

162
00:16:17,831 --> 00:16:18,732
I'm the one...

163
00:16:19,533 --> 00:16:21,201
who will be your memory for you.

164
00:16:40,587 --> 00:16:41,221
Tao Sor.

165
00:16:46,627 --> 00:16:47,761
I'm Talay.

166
00:16:48,629 --> 00:16:49,897
I'm your older brother.

167
00:16:51,798 --> 00:16:52,666
Is something wrong?

168
00:17:04,578 --> 00:17:06,146
I wanna sleep some more.

169
00:17:06,914 --> 00:17:09,182
I wanna dream about him and who he is.

170
00:17:41,148 --> 00:17:41,949
Tao Sor,

171
00:17:43,550 --> 00:17:44,918
aren't you gonna eat?

172
00:17:52,426 --> 00:17:53,360
Talay?

173
00:17:54,795 --> 00:17:56,663
Do you know the person in this picture?

174
00:18:01,335 --> 00:18:02,736
Why...

175
00:18:03,370 --> 00:18:05,072
did I draw him so much?

176
00:18:06,139 --> 00:18:07,674
That means...

177
00:18:09,343 --> 00:18:11,678
he means a lot to me, right?

178
00:18:18,852 --> 00:18:19,553
That's not it.

179
00:18:20,721 --> 00:18:23,724
You were just..drawing from experience.

180
00:18:25,158 --> 00:18:25,993
Oh!

181
00:18:27,194 --> 00:18:29,029
Mor Kluen once said that,

182
00:18:29,396 --> 00:18:31,398
if we do things repeatedly over and over again,

183
00:18:32,199 --> 00:18:33,900
our bodies will remember....

184
00:18:35,636 --> 00:18:37,771
That's why you...

185
00:18:38,572 --> 00:18:42,142
That's why you draw these pictures over and over again.

186
00:18:44,177 --> 00:18:45,512
Mor Kluen...

187
00:18:46,947 --> 00:18:47,881
who's that?

188
00:18:51,118 --> 00:18:52,552
Mor Kluen's...

189
00:18:52,986 --> 00:18:55,122
is your regular doctor.

190
00:19:05,666 --> 00:19:07,467
I really don't know this person?

191
00:19:12,873 --> 00:19:13,740
How about this?

192
00:19:14,675 --> 00:19:16,076
I'll get Mor Kluen here,

193
00:19:16,643 --> 00:19:17,544
try talking to him.

194
00:19:17,811 --> 00:19:19,579
Maybe that might ease your mind.

195
00:19:20,380 --> 00:19:21,148
Okay.

196
00:19:22,716 --> 00:19:23,583
Thank you.

197
00:19:31,792 --> 00:19:32,759
Shall we go eat?

198
00:19:45,357 --> 00:19:46,358
Mor...

199
00:19:47,059 --> 00:19:48,460
is there any way...

200
00:19:49,394 --> 00:19:51,963
that we can get Kim out of Tao Sor's memories?

201
00:19:52,597 --> 00:19:56,268
You're talking about something that even renowned doctors and professors can't do.

202
00:19:56,601 --> 00:19:58,203
You can stop anyone from doing whatever you want,

203
00:19:58,804 --> 00:20:01,473
but the one thing you can't stop anyone from doing...

204
00:20:01,673 --> 00:20:04,176
even yourself, is thinking.

205
00:20:05,577 --> 00:20:07,913
Mor, I know!

206
00:20:08,380 --> 00:20:10,816
My family's not ready for that kind of loss again!

207
00:20:11,917 --> 00:20:14,119
Fine, I'll talk to him.

208
00:20:14,352 --> 00:20:15,821
But right now, I'm busy.

209
00:20:16,221 --> 00:20:18,156
There's doctors here for seminars everywhere.

210
00:20:18,356 --> 00:20:20,759
Can you get Tao Sor to come see me in the city?

211
00:20:21,126 --> 00:20:24,963
Let him go outside for a change, it might help with his mood.

212
00:20:43,323 --> 00:20:46,293
These dreams are the only things I can remember.

213
00:20:47,649 --> 00:20:48,616
Also...

214
00:20:49,451 --> 00:20:50,819
I dream about this man...

215
00:20:52,287 --> 00:20:53,888
I've drawn so many pictures of him...

216
00:20:54,322 --> 00:20:55,457
That means...

217
00:20:56,191 --> 00:20:57,926
I've dreamt about him many times

218
00:20:58,526 --> 00:20:59,461
but...

219
00:21:01,062 --> 00:21:05,100
I ask Talay, and he says that I don't know him.

220
00:21:08,336 --> 00:21:10,071
I want to see him.

221
00:21:13,708 --> 00:21:16,244
I know, but I'm not ready yet!

222
00:21:17,245 --> 00:21:20,248
My family's not ready for any more risks.

223
00:21:22,851 --> 00:21:24,919
And what if in the end...

224
00:21:29,591 --> 00:21:31,559
everything was just a thought?

225
00:21:35,764 --> 00:21:36,664
Like how?

226
00:21:38,733 --> 00:21:40,668
In psychology...

227
00:21:41,302 --> 00:21:44,439
sometimes the things we dream or imagine...

228
00:21:44,806 --> 00:21:49,377
might come from deep desires that we can't experience in the real world.

229
00:21:50,145 --> 00:21:51,946
In your case,

230
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:54,883
some things are similar to some triggers known as:

231
00:21:55,583 --> 00:21:57,619
Daydreaming in Compositon.

232
00:21:58,386 --> 00:22:02,924
It's using the images in our heads and dreams to replace our desires,

233
00:22:03,258 --> 00:22:04,559
but they don't really exist.

234
00:22:09,030 --> 00:22:10,498
Sometimes...

235
00:22:11,199 --> 00:22:13,334
it could point to a phenomenon called:

236
00:22:14,369 --> 00:22:15,670
Conafabulation.

237
00:22:16,404 --> 00:22:21,709
It's when we fill our memories with certain images, while we are unaware of it happening.

238
00:22:22,944 --> 00:22:26,014
Which could come from incomplete memories...

239
00:22:26,748 --> 00:22:30,952
or feelings of emptiness inside.

240
00:22:36,324 --> 00:22:37,292
That means..

241
00:22:38,560 --> 00:22:40,328
all of this is a lie?

242
00:22:43,731 --> 00:22:45,767
It's not a lie, Tao SOr.

243
00:22:45,967 --> 00:22:49,737
But it's your brain trying to create the perfect image.

244
00:22:49,871 --> 00:22:53,208
So you can feel like there is continuity in your life through drawings.

245
00:22:53,575 --> 00:22:55,743
Or maybe it can deeply reflect

246
00:22:56,010 --> 00:22:58,213
how you want an intimate relationship

247
00:22:58,580 --> 00:23:00,014
how you might want a lover

248
00:23:00,415 --> 00:23:02,851
but since there's nothing in your life that is similar,

249
00:23:03,084 --> 00:23:06,087
you expressed that need through drawings.

250
00:23:13,695 --> 00:23:15,029
And...

251
00:23:16,497 --> 00:23:17,866
did I ever love someone?

252
00:23:21,903 --> 00:23:23,471
You love your dad,

253
00:23:23,805 --> 00:23:25,006
your mom,

254
00:23:25,607 --> 00:23:27,108
and Talay.

255
00:23:28,176 --> 00:23:30,478
And everyone around you,

256
00:23:30,745 --> 00:23:32,981
they all love and care about you very much.

257
00:23:33,982 --> 00:23:36,451
Shall we try being happy with the present?

258
00:23:41,589 --> 00:23:42,690
Is that better?

259
00:23:45,059 --> 00:23:46,461
Thank you.

260
00:24:10,057 --> 00:24:12,593
Anything else? I'm gonna leave soon.

261
00:24:13,994 --> 00:24:15,929
Hold on, Daiji...

262
00:24:20,834 --> 00:24:22,069
I can't remember anything...

263
00:24:24,204 --> 00:24:25,005
but...

264
00:24:26,740 --> 00:24:28,775
dreams are the only thing that I can remember.

265
00:24:32,379 --> 00:24:34,348
I always dream about that man.

266
00:24:36,250 --> 00:24:37,885
But he isn't real...

267
00:24:43,524 --> 00:24:45,025
It's like I...

268
00:24:45,526 --> 00:24:47,027
have nothing left.

269
00:24:51,932 --> 00:24:53,567
I don't want to dream of him anymore.

270
00:24:55,269 --> 00:24:56,470
But...

271
00:24:57,571 --> 00:24:59,072
I can't help but feel...

272
00:25:00,707 --> 00:25:02,442
like I want to see him all the time.

273
00:25:03,110 --> 00:25:04,945
Calm down for now.

274
00:25:08,148 --> 00:25:09,850
I'm sorry for...

275
00:25:10,651 --> 00:25:12,586
venting to you.
- It's okay.

276
00:25:13,186 --> 00:25:15,188
I understand, I really do.

277
00:25:16,924 --> 00:25:18,525
Umm, wait a minute.

278
00:25:34,107 --> 00:25:37,110
Please...throw these away for me.

279
00:25:38,111 --> 00:25:39,513
Because in the end...

280
00:25:39,846 --> 00:25:42,015
these aren't my real memories.

281
00:25:43,650 --> 00:25:45,385
Like Kluen said...

282
00:25:47,020 --> 00:25:48,255
we should be in the present.

283
00:25:48,822 --> 00:25:49,623
Get rid of it?

284
00:25:51,692 --> 00:25:52,292
Yes.

285
00:25:53,594 --> 00:25:55,062
Because in any case,

286
00:25:55,862 --> 00:25:56,763
when I wake up...

287
00:25:58,031 --> 00:25:59,499
I'll just forget it all.

288
00:26:03,503 --> 00:26:04,671
Wait a minute.

289
00:26:19,486 --> 00:26:20,253
Hold on to them.

290
00:26:24,391 --> 00:26:27,361
Eitherway, they're still your memories.

291
00:26:30,297 --> 00:26:31,365
I'm off.

292
00:27:14,975 --> 00:27:16,677
What's the matter with Kim?

293
00:27:17,284 --> 00:27:19,386
He's been acting like this for weeks.

294
00:27:20,187 --> 00:27:21,922
When is it going to end?

295
00:27:22,522 --> 00:27:25,525
If it's gonna be like this, I think we should send him back to Bangkok.

296
00:27:27,828 --> 00:27:29,963
I'll try talking to him, Dad.

297
00:27:31,498 --> 00:27:34,534
I'll leave it you. I'll go take care of business first.

298
00:27:55,922 --> 00:27:58,191
There's 2 ships coming in tomorrow,

299
00:27:58,725 --> 00:28:02,028
take your pick, the Western clients or the Chinese ones.

300
00:28:08,168 --> 00:28:10,737
Are you just gonna be sitting and sleeping around like this?

301
00:28:11,638 --> 00:28:13,373
You must be glad.

302
00:28:14,674 --> 00:28:16,643
When I first got here,

303
00:28:18,311 --> 00:28:20,480
you wanted things to be like this, didn't you?

304
00:28:28,989 --> 00:28:31,992
You should just move on, Kim.

305
00:28:33,326 --> 00:28:36,897
Once you get back to Bangkok, you're gonna get to start over!

306
00:28:39,165 --> 00:28:40,901
Forgetting someone for you,

307
00:28:42,202 --> 00:28:43,737
is so easy for you, right?

308
00:28:51,311 --> 00:28:52,646
What do you mean by that?

309
00:28:54,948 --> 00:28:57,317
Like how you don't talk about when we were young.

310
00:28:59,252 --> 00:29:01,788
You act as if he was never in our lives.

311
00:29:03,056 --> 00:29:04,691
Even someone you grew up together with,

312
00:29:05,959 --> 00:29:07,193
you're still able to forget them.

313
00:29:08,361 --> 00:29:09,596
If you don't know anything, then don't say anything.

314
00:29:10,096 --> 00:29:11,031
But isn't it true?

315
00:29:12,732 --> 00:29:14,801
We lived in this house together for so long,

316
00:29:16,269 --> 00:29:17,938
But since I came back here,

317
00:29:19,439 --> 00:29:20,840
I'm asking you for real,

318
00:29:23,109 --> 00:29:24,511
have you ever thought about him?

319
00:29:29,449 --> 00:29:31,618
Some things, though we never talk about them

320
00:29:32,852 --> 00:29:34,321
it doesn't mean that we've forgotten!

321
00:29:38,124 --> 00:29:39,292
Why wouldn't I remember?

322
00:29:40,093 --> 00:29:42,228
That the other day was his birthday?!

323
00:29:44,197 --> 00:29:45,932
How could I forget?!

324
00:29:48,134 --> 00:29:49,936
What he liked to eat...

325
00:29:55,875 --> 00:29:57,510
But some memories...

326
00:29:58,912 --> 00:30:00,413
can destroy us, you know?

327
00:30:16,596 --> 00:30:19,132
Sang, are you okay?

328
00:30:19,899 --> 00:30:21,334
I'm okay.

329
00:30:21,668 --> 00:30:23,970
You don't have to go, I'll take the clients myself.

330
00:30:25,171 --> 00:30:26,606
But this job's...
- Go home.

331
00:30:26,873 --> 00:30:27,640
It's okay.

332
00:30:28,375 --> 00:30:29,609
You've been tired all day,

333
00:30:29,909 --> 00:30:31,911
if I get any tips, I'll share them with you.

334
00:30:34,581 --> 00:30:36,816
Okay, bro. Thanks so much!

335
00:30:38,084 --> 00:30:41,955
I wanna have Mie Hokkien, Sang. Can you get some for me?
I'll eat when I get back home.

336
00:30:42,756 --> 00:30:44,758
Sure, I'll get you 3 servings!

337
00:30:45,058 --> 00:30:46,926
Great. Then I'll get going, okay?

338
00:30:49,596 --> 00:30:50,563
Look after yourself!

339
00:30:51,998 --> 00:30:54,200
Hurry back, okay?

340
00:31:10,316 --> 00:31:11,351
The truth is...

341
00:31:12,852 --> 00:31:14,921
the one who should have died that day...

342
00:31:16,856 --> 00:31:18,291
it should have been me!

343
00:31:20,126 --> 00:31:21,895
It should have been me!
- Sang!

344
00:31:22,195 --> 00:31:24,998
It should have been me that died!
- Sang!

345
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:29,169
I should have been the one that died!

346
00:31:29,803 --> 00:31:30,470
Sang!

347
00:31:33,673 --> 00:31:35,175
I'm sorry.

348
00:31:38,878 --> 00:31:40,213
I'm sorry too!

349
00:31:41,915 --> 00:31:43,249
I'm sorry!

350
00:31:44,350 --> 00:31:45,718
I'm the one...

351
00:31:46,319 --> 00:31:48,088
who never knew how you felt.

352
00:31:53,660 --> 00:31:54,961
I'm sorry....

353
00:31:57,797 --> 00:31:59,132
I'm sorry, Sang...

354
00:32:13,913 --> 00:32:15,048
Something going on?

355
00:32:25,125 --> 00:32:26,192
Little bit...

356
00:32:30,563 --> 00:32:31,431
Siw...

357
00:32:32,765 --> 00:32:35,468
Can I have you look after the office for Sang?

358
00:33:28,555 --> 00:33:31,090
We're closing, please come back tomorrow.

359
00:33:31,357 --> 00:33:33,193
Then I'll come back tomorrow.

360
00:33:36,596 --> 00:33:37,597
Nao!

361
00:33:38,598 --> 00:33:41,401
Why didn't say you were coming? I could've picked you up!

362
00:33:41,801 --> 00:33:42,835
I'm here to surpise you.

363
00:33:43,169 --> 00:33:45,405
Here, I got you some snacks from Bangkok.

364
00:33:46,439 --> 00:33:47,407
Thank you!

365
00:33:48,107 --> 00:33:49,876
So are you here on a trip?

366
00:33:50,210 --> 00:33:51,244
How many days will you stay?

367
00:33:51,711 --> 00:33:54,714
This time might be a bit long, I got a new job too.

368
00:33:55,148 --> 00:33:56,015
A job?

369
00:33:57,817 --> 00:34:00,353
Yes, I was thinking of asking you to help too.

370
00:34:00,720 --> 00:34:03,289
Remember Future, the mall owner's daughter?

371
00:34:04,290 --> 00:34:06,492
Her dad had me tell their fortune.

372
00:34:06,726 --> 00:34:09,996
After talking for a while, we got to the topic of natural disasters in Phuket.

373
00:34:11,564 --> 00:34:15,368
So he wanted to create content to inform people about natural disasters

374
00:34:15,368 --> 00:34:16,603
that affect people greatly.

375
00:34:16,936 --> 00:34:20,540
So I told him that I knew a Content Creator that's also a local.

376
00:34:20,873 --> 00:34:21,674
Me?

377
00:34:22,375 --> 00:34:24,277
Yes, but I'll be your assistant.

378
00:34:28,081 --> 00:34:29,716
Actually, that's a good idea.

379
00:34:30,016 --> 00:34:32,085
We can promote Siam Sea as well.

380
00:34:32,685 --> 00:34:34,320
So people can know that Siam Sea...

381
00:34:34,854 --> 00:34:36,923
promotes safe tourism.

382
00:34:38,725 --> 00:34:40,994
And can we handle doing this on our own?

383
00:34:44,697 --> 00:34:46,199
It's actually 3.

384
00:34:49,335 --> 00:34:50,003
I think...

385
00:34:50,203 --> 00:34:53,673
we can start from looking at Siam Sea's past ventures?

386
00:34:53,873 --> 00:34:57,677
Look for reports of storms, accidents, and the like.

387
00:34:59,479 --> 00:35:03,116
About the people who've had direct experience,

388
00:35:03,416 --> 00:35:05,151
would there be anyone still alive?

389
00:35:07,387 --> 00:35:10,857
In that case, I'll make some calls and see if we can get some info.

390
00:35:13,059 --> 00:35:14,360
Yeah, speaking of...

391
00:35:14,594 --> 00:35:18,364
The youngest son from the Precious Resort family, has also been through an accident.

392
00:35:19,732 --> 00:35:22,468
Hmm, should we go interview him?

393
00:35:23,936 --> 00:35:25,204
Even if you asked,

394
00:35:25,738 --> 00:35:27,273
Tao Sor wouldn't remember anything.

395
00:35:27,674 --> 00:35:29,375
As for Talay...

396
00:35:31,911 --> 00:35:32,845
he won't tell us anything.

397
00:35:34,080 --> 00:35:35,348
You're right about that...

398
00:35:36,482 --> 00:35:39,118
But the people there might know something?

399
00:35:42,855 --> 00:35:43,723
What about Daiji?

400
00:35:43,923 --> 00:35:45,992
The one that's always with Tao Sor.

401
00:35:48,995 --> 00:35:51,631
Well, that person could be possible.

402
00:35:52,031 --> 00:35:53,933
Shall we go try and interview him?

403
00:35:57,970 --> 00:35:58,738
I think...

404
00:35:59,639 --> 00:36:00,673
you should go by yourselves.

405
00:36:01,207 --> 00:36:04,210
Huh? Why? You don't wanna see him?

406
00:36:09,415 --> 00:36:13,219
Up to you then. If you wanna just let time pass by you,

407
00:36:13,319 --> 00:36:16,989
then go back to Bangkok, act as if nothing happened...

408
00:36:16,989 --> 00:36:17,957
that's your choice.

409
00:36:18,458 --> 00:36:21,427
Let's go, Nao. Don't give him any attention.

410
00:36:51,224 --> 00:36:52,291
Siw-chan!

411
00:36:52,859 --> 00:36:54,427
It's been a long time, Prof!

412
00:36:54,627 --> 00:36:55,962
Get anything today?

413
00:36:57,497 --> 00:36:58,598
Not yet...

414
00:37:00,666 --> 00:37:02,802
And... Tao Sor didn't come today?

415
00:37:03,536 --> 00:37:04,270
He didn't.

416
00:37:04,704 --> 00:37:05,905
He had soemthing else he wanted to do.

417
00:37:06,839 --> 00:37:08,841
Umm, Daiji?
- Hmm?

418
00:37:08,841 --> 00:37:10,910
I have something I wanna ask.

419
00:37:12,145 --> 00:37:13,813
Of course...

420
00:37:56,856 --> 00:37:58,591
Me being able to meet you...

421
00:37:58,891 --> 00:38:00,693
is one of the best things that's ever happened to me.

422
00:38:06,065 --> 00:38:06,866
And...

423
00:38:07,366 --> 00:38:10,369
how would you know if you've ever experienced anything good before?

424
00:38:11,370 --> 00:38:15,341
Some day, I'll take you to my studio.

425
00:38:15,775 --> 00:38:17,043
if I remember to.

426
00:38:17,944 --> 00:38:20,480
Deal! Because if you don't remember,

427
00:38:21,080 --> 00:38:22,748
I'll go to your place myself!

428
00:38:24,750 --> 00:38:27,453
Kim. When I wake up,

429
00:38:28,454 --> 00:38:29,989
will I remember you?

430
00:38:30,890 --> 00:38:33,726
I told you already, you don't have to worry about that.

431
00:38:34,293 --> 00:38:35,828
Even if you won't remember,

432
00:38:36,028 --> 00:38:40,132
I'll be here, re-introducing myself each time.

433
00:38:41,934 --> 00:38:44,937
Trust me, okay? Get some rest.

434
00:38:56,983 --> 00:38:58,985
I love you, Kim.

435
00:39:25,111 --> 00:39:26,379
Kim!

436
00:39:30,816 --> 00:39:31,684
Kim!

437
00:39:35,021 --> 00:39:35,855
Tao Sor!

438
00:39:38,724 --> 00:39:39,559
Tao Sor!

439
00:39:40,026 --> 00:39:41,027
You remember me!

440
00:39:41,861 --> 00:39:42,862
You remember me, right?

441
00:39:49,802 --> 00:39:50,736
Not really.

442
00:39:52,738 --> 00:39:53,806
I can't remember...

443
00:39:55,341 --> 00:39:56,242
But...

444
00:40:04,216 --> 00:40:06,385
your tattoo and mine...

445
00:40:13,092 --> 00:40:14,327
I know you, right?

446
00:40:15,161 --> 00:40:18,164
And we also have memories together...

447
00:40:20,266 --> 00:40:20,900
right?

448
00:40:22,068 --> 00:40:22,768
Yes!

449
00:41:46,719 --> 00:41:50,523
That means I'm not really your son, right?

450
00:41:54,460 --> 00:41:55,995
I don't know why...

451
00:41:57,363 --> 00:41:59,465
I'm even alive.

452
00:42:01,634 --> 00:42:03,602
You're here so we can love each other.

453
00:42:04,904 --> 00:42:06,672
Why the fuck are you helping Kim?!

454
00:42:07,073 --> 00:42:08,307
The perosn that destroyed everything....

455
00:42:08,541 --> 00:42:09,308
isn't me...

456
00:42:10,176 --> 00:42:11,277
but you!

457
00:42:11,777 --> 00:42:13,279
I still want to see you...

458
00:42:14,914 --> 00:42:16,449
Please don't leave me.

